\":\"in_progress\"}}\n./runs/sessions/phase13b-oob-fix.jsonl:70:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_36\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"sed -n '120,160p' GAME_DESIGN.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"## 7. Effect Vocabulary [HARD — the Director's verbs]\\n\\nThe atomic effects from which **all** items, enemy abilities, traps, and shrine-like\\ninteractions are composed. ~16 verbs; each takes bounded parameters. This list is\\nthe single most load-bearing table in the project: the engine implements exactly\\nthese, and the Director's creativity is names + fiction + composition + parameters.\\n\\n| Verb | Parameters (bounds [HARD]) | Notes |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| `damage` | amount 1–12 | |\\n| `heal` | amount 1–20 | |\\n| `apply_status` | status (from §6), duration (per §6) | |\\n| `cure_status` | one status or `all` | |\\n| `buff_stat` | ATK or DEF, ±1–3, duration 5–20 | |\\n| `nutrition` | +10–100 Fullness | |\\n| `teleport_self` | random walkable cell | escape valve |\\n| `teleport_target` | random walkable cell | |\\n| `blink` | directed hop 2–4 tiles | |\\n| `knockback` | push 1–3 tiles, collision = 1–3 dmg | |\\n| `reveal` | map / items / enemies / traps (this floor) | |\\n| `identify` | one carried item, or all of one category | |\\n| `enchant` | weapon or armor, +1 (item cap +3) | |\\n| `summon` | 1–3 entities **from this floor's roster**, adjacent cells | no novel entities mid-floor |\\n| `transform` | re-roll target enemy into roster entity of ≤ equal budget cost | |\\n| `dig` | remove wall tiles in a line, length 1–5 | |\\n\\n**Composition rules:** an item or ability bundles **1–3 effects** + one **trigger**\\n+ one **targeting shape**.\\n\\n- Triggers: `quaff`, `read`, `throw_hit`, `equip_passive`, `on_hit` (weapon proc,\\n  chance 10–30% [HARD]), `on_struck` (armor proc, same), `step` (trap), `use`\\n  (tool, 1–5 charges).\\n- Targeting shapes: `self`, `melee`, `bolt` (first target in line, range 3–8),\\n  `burst` (radius 1–2, centered self or impact), `floor`.\\n\\nGrowing this vocabulary is the **intended** post-MVP expansion axis: add a verb to\\nthe engine (with tests), bump the protocol version, and the Director's expressive\\nspace multiplies. Verbs are added by humans via this file, never by the Director.\\n\\n## 8. Items and the Economy\\n\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n./pnpm-lock.yaml:220:  '@types/esrecurse@4.3.1':\n./pnpm-lock.yaml:412:  esrecurse@4.3.0:\n./pnpm-lock.yaml:971:  '@types/esrecurse@4.3.1': {}\n./pnpm-lock.yaml:1158:      '@types/esrecurse': 4.3.1\n./pnpm-lock.yaml:1160:      esrecurse: 4.3.0\n./pnpm-lock.yaml:1212:  esrecurse@4.3.0:\n./runs/briefs/phase06-state.md:1:IMPLEMENT TASK — PHASE-06: engine state model & serialization (contract: phase-plans/PHASE-06-ENGINE-STATE.md; read it plus TECH_SPEC.md §2/§9 and GAME_DESIGN.md §2/§4 first).\n./phase-plans/PHASE-17-FLOOR-GENERATION.md:7:GAME_DESIGN §2 (geometry table, layout flavors, solvability guarantee [HARD]); TECH_SPEC §9 (seeded); NORTH_STAR §3 (layout parameters are Director-authorable).\n./docs/progress-archive/WAVE-A.md:12:| 04B-1 | Config module ([T]/[HARD] transcription) | Codex | main (src/config) | ready-for-verify | 2 doc ambiguities → orchestrator pinned in GAME_DESIGN |\n./docs/progress-archive/WAVE-A.md:34:| 2026-06-11 | — | claude (orchestrator) | Doc spine created: NORTH_STAR, CLAUDE, AGENTS, TECH_SPEC, UX, WORLD, GAME_DESIGN, PROGRESS, PHASE-00 | this commit |\n./phase-plans/PHASE-32-PROMPT-ASSEMBLY.md:7:WORLD §10 (hard canon → prompt), §3 (Director persona traits), §8 (depth-arc personalization); NORTH_STAR §6 (the floor responds to the trace); 23A traces as input.\n./phase-plans/PHASE-13A-EFFECTS-CORE.md:7:GAME_DESIGN §7 (verbs + bounds + composition); schemas from 05 are the input type — the interpreter executes validated effect bundles, never raw data.\n./phase-plans/PHASE-13A-EFFECTS-CORE.md:27:| 2 | verify | Per-verb audit vs GAME_DESIGN §7 rows; bounds re