rtial\\nStarted: <YYYY-MM-DD>\\nLast updated: <YYYY-MM-DD>\\n\\nPlan:\\n- <planned step or deliverable>\\n\\nCurrent checkpoint:\\n- <what has been done so far or what is about to start>\\n\\nValidation:\\n- <planned command/check> -> not run yet\\n\\nOut-of-scope / future work:\\n- <future task, reason it is out of current phase, suggested phase if known>\\n```\\n\\nUse the repository's existing `PROGRESS.md` style if one already exists.\\n\\n## During Execution\\n\\nUpdate `PROGRESS.md` at meaningful checkpoints:\\n\\n- After planning is translated into concrete steps.\\n- After each major deliverable or subtask completes.\\n- Before switching from implementation to validation.\\n- After validation passes, fails, or is blocked.\\n- When discovering a scope mismatch, prerequisite gap, or environment blocker.\\n- Before final response if the user asked for frequent progress updates.\\n\\nKeep entries factual. Do not mark a step complete until the relevant files, artifacts, or checks support it.\\n\\n## Completion Update\\n\\nWhen the whole phase appears complete:\\n\\n1. Re-read the phase plan and compare it to the implementation.\\n2. Update `PROGRESS.md` with final status, completed deliverables, validation results, and any deviations.\\n3. If validation is blocked, mark the phase `Validation blocked` or `Partial`, not `Complete`.\\n4. Include exact commands run and short results.\\n5. Include generated evidence paths when the phase produces traces, scorecards, reviews, changelogs, or similar artifacts.\\n\\nDo not claim phase completion in chat until `PROGRESS.md` reflects the same state.\\n\\n## Out-of-Scope And Future Work\\n\\nWhen work is useful but outside the current phase:\\n\\n- Do not implement it unless the user expands scope.\\n- Add it under `Out-of-scope / future work`.\\n- State why it is outside the current phase.\\n- Link it to a future phase or category when obvious.\\n- Keep it separate from blockers. A future task should not make the current phase incomplete unless the phase plan requires it.\\n\\nExample:\\n\\n```markdown\\nOut-of-scope / future work:\\n- Add browser UI polish. Outside PHASE-04A because this phase only defines ASCII rendering; candidate for PHASE-08A.\\n- Add extra enemy archetypes. Outside current minimal dungeon scope; candidate for enemy variety phase.\\n```\\n\\n## Edit Rules\\n\\n- Preserve existing progress history.\\n- Prefer appending or updating the active phase section over rewriting the whole file.\\n- Keep timestamps concrete using the current local date.\\n- Separate planned, in-progress, complete, blocked, and future-work states.\\n- Avoid optimistic language that is not backed by files, tests, or artifacts.\\n/Users/keigoshimada/Documents/generative-gaming\\nENVIRONMENT.md\\nGAME_DESIGN.md\\nNORTH_STAR.md\\nPROGRESS.md\\nphase-plans/PHASE-13B-EFFECTS-SPATIAL.md\\nsrc/engine/clock/clock.test.ts\\nsrc/engine/clock/index.ts\\nsrc/engine/effects/core.test.ts\\nsrc/engine/effects/core.ts\\nsrc/engine/effects/geometry.test.ts\\nsrc/engine/effects/geometry.ts\\nsrc/engine/effects/registry.test.ts\\nsrc/engine/effects/registry.ts\\nsrc/engine/index.test.ts\\nsrc/engine/index.ts\\nsrc/engine/map/fov.test.ts\\nsrc/engine/map/fov.ts\\nsrc/engine/map/grid.test.ts\\nsrc/engine/map/grid.ts\\nsrc/engine/map/index.ts\\nsrc/engine/map/path.test.ts\\nsrc/engine/map/path.ts\\nsrc/engine/map/terrain.test.ts\\nsrc/engine/map/terrain.ts\\nsrc/engine/rng/index.ts\\nsrc/engine/rng/rng.test.ts\\nsrc/engine/state/index.ts\\nsrc/engine/state/init.ts\\nsrc/engine/state/node-fs.d.ts\\nsrc/engine/state/serialize.ts\\nsrc/engine/state/state.test.ts\\nsrc/engine/state/types.ts\\nsrc/engine/systems/combat.test.ts\\nsrc/engine/systems/combat.ts\\nsrc/engine/systems/inventory.test.ts\\nsrc/engine/systems/inventory.ts\\nsrc/engine/systems/movement.test.ts\\nsrc/engine/systems/movement.ts\\nsrc/engine/systems/player.test.ts\\nsrc/engine/systems/player.ts\\nsrc/engine/systems/status.test.ts\\nsrc/engine/system